narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You're writing a senior thesis and you think it'll go smoothly. It won't. This course makes you work when you don't want to, and that's the important part because when you're lazy you need a little kick in the ass.
If you're a Senior AMST major, you don't have a choice but to take it...

Meet every other week to discuss and work on research techniques; share progress with other AMST students; break up into writing groups to do a more focused critique. I would recommend this course - it's required for full-year projects, but even for half-year, it's a good idea. It keeps you on track.
